.Dd February 23, 2026
.Dt WINDOWS 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm windows
.Nd overview and select Wayland toplevel windows
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl h
.Op Fl o Ar output
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
program is a Wayland client that presents an overview of all toplevel
windows on a designated output monitor and allows interactive
selection of a window.
.Pp
The program connects to the Wayland compositor, enumerates available
toplevel surfaces, captures their contents in shared memory buffers,
and arranges them using an exposé-style layout.  The selected window's
toplevel handle identifier is written to
.Xr stdout 3
when confirmed.
.Pp
If no valid output monitor is specified, or the designated monitor
cannot be resolved to a known output, the program
.Xr exit 3
with a non-zero status.
.Bl -tag
.It Fl h
Print the help message and quit.
.It Fl o Ar output
Configure the designated output monitor.  This is case-sensitive and
must match the output name reported by the compositor.
.El
.Pp
The Wayland compositor must support at least the following protocols
and interface versions:
.TS
BOX CENTER TAB(;);
cb|cb, l|c.
Protocol;Version
_
wl_output;4
wl_seat;7
wl_shm;1
wl_compositor;4
ext_foreign_toplevel_list;1
ext_image_copy_capture_manager;1
ext_foreign_toplevel_image_capture_source_manager;1
wp_fractional_scale_manager;1
wp_viewporter;1
xdg_wm_base;3
.TE
.Sh INTERACTION
.Bl -tag
.It Ao left Ac , Ao right Ac , Ao up Ac , Aq down
Move focus between the windows according to their layout adjacency.
An initial keypress selects the top-left window.
.It Aq enter
Print the toplevel handle identifier of the focused window to
.Va stdout
and quit.  Do nothing when there is no focused window.
.It Aq escape
Quit without doing anything.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag
.It 0
Successful execution.
.It 1
Invalid option(s) or failure to resolve the designated monitor.
.El
